One insurgent has been killed in an operation to repel rampaging Boko Haram at Gamboru-Ngala, Borno State. The Director, Army Public Relations, Brig.-Gen. Texas Chukwu, said yesterday that several others fled in the operation. A soldier however died during the operation. Chukwu said the troops recovered one Rocket Propelled gun, one anti-aircraft gun, two AK 47 rifles and two empty magazines. The army spokesman called on the people to cooperate with troops, provide useful and timely information to security agencies. 